2010年，澳大利亞政府宣布，將投入2,000萬[[澳元|澳元]]來進行詳細的高速鐵路可行性評估與路廊研究，以評估確認興建的經濟效益以及東海岸潛在高鐵路廊網絡的規劃。<ref name="Moving forward with high speed rail">{{cite web|last=Albanese|first=Anthony|title=Moving forward with high speed rail|url=http://anthonyalbanese.com.au/moving-forward-with-high-speed-rail-2|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130309004837/http://anthonyalbanese.com.au/moving-forward-with-high-speed-rail-2|archivedate=2013年3月9日|publisher=Anthony Albanese MP|accessdate=2012年10月5日|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 第一階段的可行性評估在2011年完成，當時評估認為，興建費用可能約610億到1,080億澳元，這取決於所選擇的路廊以及沿線設置車站數量。{{sfn|High Speed Rail Study Phase 1|2011}}<ref>{{citation | title = High speed rail study underway | publisher = [[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Australian Broadcasting Corporation]] | date = 2011年2月2日 | url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2011/02/02/3127446.htm?site=newcastle | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121112085905/http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2011/02/02/3127446.htm?site=newcastle | archivedate = 2012年11月12日 | deadurl = yes }}</ref><ref name=Saulwick>{{cite news | url = http://www.smh.com.au/national/highspeed-rail-too-costly-study-finds-20100927-15u5s.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121107055422/http://www.smh.com.au/national/highspeed-rail-too-costly-study-finds-20100927-15u5s.html | archivedate = 2012年11月7日 | title = High speed rail between Sydney and Melbourne too expensive | first = Jacol | last = Saulwick | publisher = [[Sydney_Morning_Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]] | date = 2010年9月28日 | accessdate = 2010年10月17日 | deadurl = yes }}</ref> 第二階段可行性評估報告在2013年4月公布，報告中列出了更詳細的高鐵興建費用，預估將高達1,140億澳元，预计2027年动工，2058年完工，2065年完全营运。建成后，布里斯班到悉尼2小时37分钟（797公里），悉尼到墨尔本2小时44分钟（824公里）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infrastructure.gov.au/rail/trains/high_speed/index.aspx|title=Phase 2 high speed rail study| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814201622/http://www.infrastructure.gov.au/rail/trains/high_speed/index.aspx| archivedate=2013年8月14日|work={{ URL | http://www.infrastructure.gov.au | Australian Government Department of Infrastructure and Transport }}|publisher=|accessdate=2013年4月12日|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 

澳大利亞鐵路的最高時速，是1998年[[昆士蘭|昆士蘭]][[傾斜式列車|傾斜列車]]實驗的210 km/h<ref name=SMHSpeedFreakMarch2013>{{cite web|title=Speed freak|url=http://www.smh.com.au/travel/speed-freak-20130301-2faha.html|publisher=The Sydney Morning Herald|accessdate=2013年3月16日|author=Stephen Lacey|date=2013年3月3日|archive-date=2014年2月27日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227150522/http://www.smh.com.au/travel/speed-freak-20130301-2faha.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而這僅達到國際公認高鐵定義的200 km/h（120英哩）時速的「下限」。<ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.uic.org/spip.php?article971 |title=General definitions of highspeed |publisher=International Union of Railways |accessdate=2012年10月10日 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720214528/http://www.uic.org/spip.php?article971 |archivedate=2011年7月20日 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

==概觀==
{{Main|澳大利亞鐵路運輸歷史}}
[[File:TGV-Duplex_Paris.jpg|thumb]]的[[TGV|TGV]]鐵路服務提供法國國內與國外城市之間的快速連結]]
自1980年代開始，澳大利亞政府就持續以沿東海岸興建高速鐵路為目標進行評估與探勘。而當時，利用[[航空|航空]]進行跨州首府之間的交通方式幾乎拿下澳大利亞國內的主導地位，其餘國內鄉村地區則是以[[轎車|轎車]]作為旅遊交通工具的大宗。 鐵路運輸則是在農村與城市郊區的運輸擁有顯著的市場存在，然而，由於鐵路的慢速加上列車班次並不頻繁導致跨州首府之間鐵路運輸的市場份額非常低。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bitre.gov.au/publications/39/Files/ATS_2008.pdf|title=Australian transport statistics|format=[[Portable_Document_Format|PDF]]|publisher=Bureau of Infrastructure, Transport and Regional Economics|date=June 2008|accessdate=2 March 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420005140/http://www.bitre.gov.au/publications/39/Files/ATS_2008.pdf|archivedate=2009年4月20日}}</ref> 2013年，第二階段的可行性評估報告中指出，跨州首府之間高速鐵路所需耗費的運輸時程將可能會比航空運輸的時程來得少<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.infrastructureaustralia.gov.au/public_submissions/published/files/266_australianassociationforthestudyofpeakoilandgas_SUB.pdf|title=Peak Oil and Australia's National Infrastructure|format=[[Portable_Document_Format|PDF]]|publisher=Australian Association for the Study of Peak Oil and Gas|date=October 2008|accessdate=2 March 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090523204830/http://www.infrastructureaustralia.gov.au/public_submissions/published/files/266_australianassociationforthestudyofpeakoilandgas_SUB.pdf|archivedate=2009年5月23日}}</ref>，報告中估計以常規的高速鐵路時速與旅程時間來計算，從雪梨到墨爾本僅需要2小時44分鐘，而從雪梨到布里斯班僅需要2小時37分鐘。{{sfn|High Speed Rail Study Phase 2 Report|2013}}在經過多次的可行性評估以及多方建言後澳洲政府認為，東海岸州首府之間的高速鐵路計劃是可行的，並且，預估興建高速鐵路後將可以取代航空運輸的主導地位。<ref>{{cite conference|last1=Laird|first1=P.|last2=Michell|first2=M.|last3=Adorni-Braccesi|first3=G|year=2002|title=Sydney–Canberra–Melbourne high-speed train options|conference=25th Australasian Transport Research Forum 2–4 October|location=Canberra|url=http://www.atrf.info/papers/2002/2002_Laird_Mitchell_Adorni_Braccesi.pdf|access-date=2015-06-19|archive-date=2019-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623125613/https://www.atrf.info/papers/2002/2002_Laird_Mitchell_Adorni_Braccesi.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=May|first=Murray|year=2006|title=Aviation meets ecology—redesigning policy and practice for air transport and tourism| journal=Transport Engineering in Australia|volume=10|issue=2|pages=117–128}}</ref><ref>{{cite conference|last1=Brunello|first1=Lara R|last2=Bunker|first2=Jonathan M.|last3=Ferreira|first3=Luis|year=2006|title=Investigation to Enhance Sustainable Improvements in High Speed Rail Transportation|conference=CAITR, 6,7,8 December 2006|location=Sydney|url=http://eprints.qut.edu.au/6007/1/6007_1.pdf|access-date=2015-06-19|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801145740/http://eprints.qut.edu.au/6007/1/6007_1.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|journal=Journal of Transport Geography| volume=14| issue=6|date=November 2006| pages=437–450|title=Questioning airport expansion—A case study of Canberra International Airport|first1=Murray|last1=May|first2=Stuart B.|last2=Hill| doi=10.1016/j.jtrangeo.2005.10.004}}</ref><ref>{{cite conference|last1=Brunello|first1= Lara R|last2=Bunker|first2=Jonathan M.|last3=Ferreira|first3=Luis|last4=Ferrara|first4=Renzo |year=2008|title=Enhancing Sustainable Road and Rail Interaction|conference=Transport Research Arena Europe 2008: Greener, Safer and Smarter Road Transport for Europe, 21–24 April 2008|location=Ljubljana, Slovenia}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=A Fast Railway for the East Coast|journal=Railway Digest|date=August 2007|volume=44|issue=8}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Fast Future or a Slow Death|journal=Railway Digest|date=September 2007|volume=44|issue=9}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Fast Freight and Passengers|journal=Railway Digest|date=October 2007|volume=44|issue=10}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Mixing Fast Freight and Passenger Trains|journal=Railway Digest|date=November 2007|issue=11|volume=44}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Costing a 21st Century Railway|journal=Railway Digest|date=December 2007|volume=44|issue=12}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Fast Trains – Profit or Loss|journal=Railway Digest|date=January 2008|issue=1|volume=45}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Fast Trains – Financially Viable|journal=Railway Digest|date=February 2008|volume=45|issue=2}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Fast Trains – External Benefits|journal=Railway Digest|date=March 2008|volume=45|issue=3}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|author=Colin Butcher|url=http://www.infrastructure.gov.au/transport/publications/files/Other/other_Butcher_Colin.pdf|title=(Submission)Towards a National Land Transport Plan : A Response to the Green Paper on AUSLINK|format=[[Portable_Document_Format|PDF]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320212732/https://www.infrastructure.gov.au/transport/publications/files/Other/other_Butcher_Colin.pdf|archivedate=2012年3月20日|deadurl=yes}}</ref>{{sfn|Laird|2001}}{{sfn|High Speed Rail for Australia: An opportunity for the 21st century|2008}} 儘管這些可行性評估報告已經引起了私人企業的興趣，並且這些私人企業甚至刻意釋出評估報告來引起大眾的想像力，但至今仍沒有任何私人企業提出能夠負擔興建高速鐵路費用並且不需要政府任何補助的保證。{{sfn|East Coast Very High Speed Train Scoping Study: Phase 1 – Preliminary Study Final Report|2001|loc=section 1, page 1}}

一個運作狀況成熟的高速鐵路系統將會比航空運輸以及汽車旅遊更來得有[[經濟|經濟]][[競爭力|競爭力]]，而且，高鐵的運作不需依賴進口[[石油|石油]]，在旅遊行程上，也將比航空運輸擁有更快的運輸時間，並會減少澳洲的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]排放量{{sfn|High Speed Rail for Australia: An opportunity for the 21st century|2008}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theaustralian.news.com.au/story/0,25197,24077717-11949,00.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091019014428/http://www.theaustralian.news.com.au/story/0,25197,24077717-11949,00.html|archivedate=2009年10月19日|title=Greenhouse plans went off the rails|first=Mike|last=Steketee|publisher=News Corp Australia|newspaper=[[The_Australian|The Australian]]|date=26 July 2008|accessdate=2 March 2009|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/news/local/news/general/very-fast-train-tops-develops-wishlist/1370123.aspx|title=Very fast train tops develops' wish-list|publisher=Fairfax Media|newspaper=[[The_Canberra_Times|The Canberra Times]]|date=26 November 2008|accessdate=1 March 2009|last=Thistleton|first=John}}</ref>

