根據菲利普·萊爾德所述，避免採納高速鐵路的主要原因包括：{{sfn|Laird|2001}}
* 在國內航空旅行激烈的競爭，從而導致了高鐵票價無法提高，必須以更實惠價格吸引乘客。
* 國內過多的航空運輸補貼。
* 大型城市之間的間距因距離過於遙遠而使得高速鐵路無法對航空旅行進行有效的競爭。
* 廉價汽車旅遊的概念。
* 缺乏對大多數跨州道路的通行費。

===雅培政府時期（2013年－至今）===
2013年11月8日，作為新當選的雅培政府之中由20個政府委員會組成高鐵諮詢小組，來負責規劃的布里斯班和墨爾本之間 VFT 計畫，並確認了前代政府所留下的鑑定委員會將被清查，為的就是盡可能的削減高鐵計畫的成本並“確保政府機制是有效率以及縮編至越小越好”。<ref name=SMHnov2013>{{cite news | url = http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/tony-abbott-keeps-focus-by-cutting-bodies-past-use-by-date/story-fn59niix-1226755431163 | location = Sydney | work = The Australian | title = Tony Abbott keeps focus by cutting bodies past use-by date | first = Sid and Crowe, David | last = Marr | date = 8 November 2013 | accessdate = 8 November 2013 | archive-date = 2014-03-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140328120723/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/tony-abbott-keeps-focus-by-cutting-bodies-past-use-by-date/story-fn59niix-1226755431163 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pm.gov.au/media/2013-11-08/press-conference-melbourne | title = Media release: "Press conference, Melbourne" | publisher = Commonwealth of Australia | first = Tony | last = Abbott | date = 8 November 2013 | accessdate = 8 November 2013 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150619111402/http://www.pm.gov.au/media/2013-11-08/press-conference-melbourne | archive-date = 2015-06-19 | dead-url = yes }}</ref> 然而，在隨後的一個月，副總理沃倫·特拉斯宣布，該聯盟致力於取得前代政府的高鐵路廊確認的評估報告，並說，他個人尋求維多利亞州，新南威爾士州和昆士蘭州州長以及首都直轄區長的合作。工黨表示將支持這一舉措<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.smh.com.au/national/deputy-prime-minister-warren-truss-gets-high-speed-rail-on-track-20131201-2yjqt.html | date = 2 December 2013 | title = Deputy Prime Minister Warren Truss gets high speed rail on track | author = Ross Peake | publisher = Sydney Morning Herald | accessdate = 22 June 2014 | archive-date = 2020-11-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201128101619/https://www.smh.com.au/national/deputy-prime-minister-warren-truss-gets-high-speed-rail-on-track-20131201-2yjqt.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

在2014年，低碳倡導組織發布響應陸克文政府第2階段評估報告的詳細研究。將準備與[[德國|德國]][[德國航空太空中心|航空中心]]合作，來研究使用許多假設相同成本的方案，但以盡量減少工程費用為前提提出了一個修正路線。然而修正後的路線將更長一些（1799公里相比1748公里），不過隧道的長度減少了44％，而橋樑的長度增加了25％。大部分路廊減少的方式都是利用接入現有的大都會交通路廊之中；但當時政府評估中，選擇了政治上簡單但價格極其昂貴的[[隧道|隧道]]來連結到終點站。 因此工程計畫的提交者德魯杰拉德還批評了第2階段的評估報告中列出的45年建設時間表根本是“可笑的”。 德魯還指出，在政府報告的成本估算中有明顯的“[[鍍金|鍍金]]”疑慮。 {{en-link|BZE|Beyond Zero Emissions}}預測，高速鐵路將耗資843億澳元，並需要10年時間來興建。<ref name=BZE>{{citation | url = http://bze.org.au/media/newswire/earth-moon-8-years-melbourne-brisbane-45-130422 | title = Earth to moon in 8 years, Melbourne to Brisbane in 45 | author = Gerard Drew | publisher = Beyond Zero Emissions | accessdate = 1 March 2015 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150401172317/http://bze.org.au/media/newswire/earth-moon-8-years-melbourne-brisbane-45-130422 | archive-date = 2015-04-01 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref>{{citation | url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-11-29/high-speed-rail-cheaper-then-thought/5123966 | title = High-speed rail network $30 billion cheaper than first thought: study | publisher = ABC | author = Jake Sturmer | date = 29 November 2013 | accessdate = 1 March 2015 | archive-date = 2020-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129150710/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-11-29/high-speed-rail-cheaper-then-thought/5123966 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

